&lt;h2 style="width:450px"&gt;Getting to grips with Classes &amp; Objects&lt;/h2&gt;
You will be encountering classes and dealing with inheritance from next week and this is fundamental to how Python works. In Python, everything is an object and that means that everything â€“ absolutely everything â€“ is part of the Python class hierarchy, at the bottom of which sits the base object class.
For our purposes, the place youâ€™re going to encounter this every day is that Pandas is our main data analysis tool, but when we deal with geography weâ€™ll be using GeoPandas, which inherits from Pandas and adds (we say â€œextendsâ€) functionality for processing geo-data.
Thereâ€™s even a Moving Pandas for trajectory analysis. These all work on the basis of inheritance.
